+        ) {
+            Err(e) => println!(
+                "[4] NEG-TIE (NTT c_in[0] != SampleInBall c[0]; Tie S↔F): REJECTED at prove, {:.1?} -- {e}",
+                t.elapsed()
+            ),
+            Ok(_) => panic!("NEG-TIE must NOT produce an outer proof"),
+        }
+
+        println!(
+            "SAMPLEINBALL JOIN demonstrated: c̃ →SampleInBall→ c →forward NTT→ ĉ composed as ONE \
+             recursion tree over TWO HETEROGENEOUS gadgets (SibAir ∘ NttAir) — the challenge-polynomial \
+             construction (FIPS-204 Alg.29 Fisher-Yates placement + ball membership, reduced n=8/τ=4, \
+             real c̃-driven) landed as a real batch-STARK leg, diff-tested == reference SampleInBall, \
+             and the cross-stage tie (c S↔F) PROVEN in-circuit — the forward NTT's c is now the REAL \
+             SampleInBall output. This is the 2-stage front sub-chain c = SampleInBall(c̃) → ĉ = NTT(c)."
